{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775809883975,"sessionID":"ses_2897d33c5ffeqQ82qCou8llhnY","part":{"id":"prt_d7682d6db001APfuo4N377B9mr","messageID":"msg_d7682cd32001kGLvUR4xwq79kV","sessionID":"ses_2897d33c5ffeqQ82qCou8llhnY","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_d06fa2bb4405494a8857abff","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project structure to understand:\n1. The overall project layout, especially the `pkg/apis` directory\n2. Existing CRD type definitions and their patterns\n3. Any existing CodeInterpreter-related code or types\n4. How CRDs are typically structured in this project (look for examples like Agent, Workflow, or similar custom resources)\n5. Check if there's a `pkg/apis` directory and what's in it\n6. Look for any existing task lists or documentation about AR-002 or ST-3\n\nReturn:\n- The directory structure of pkg/apis\n- Examples of existing CRD type definitions (file paths and key patterns)\n- Any CodeInterpreter-related code found\n- The typical structure/pattern used for CRD types in this project\n- Any relevant documentation or existing task files","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_2897d12feffeGsMJVVAYuZ26jK (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nNow I have a comprehensive picture of the project. Here is my complete report:\n\n---\n\n## AgentCube Project Structure Analysis\n\n### 1. Overall Project Layout\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/\n├── .sdd_prompt.md           # SDD prompt for AR-002\n├── changes/                  # Architecture Records (ARs)\n│   ├── AR-001/              # AgentRuntime CRD (completed, Stage ST-4)\n│   │   ├── design.md\n│   │   ├── proposal.md\n│   │   └── tasks.md\n│   └── AR-002/              # CodeInterpreter CRD (Stage ST-0)\n│       ├── delta-spec.md\n│       ├── design.md\n│       ├── proposal.md\n│       └── tasks.md\n├